  {
    title: "ICF Basements & Foundations",
    description: "Muskoka's rocky terrain requires solid foundations. We build ICF basements that give you dry, energy-efficient space—even on challenging Shield lots.",
    icon: "M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5"
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How much does it cost to build a cottage in Muskoka?",
    answer: "Expect $275-$650 per square foot in Muskoka, depending on quality level. Standard grade runs $275+/sq ft. Mid-range is $410+/sq ft. High-end custom is $645+/sq ft. A 1,500 sq ft cottage typically costs $400,000-$975,000. Water-access-only properties add 15-25% due to barge logistics. Budget an additional 10% for landscaping and custom fixtures. We provide detailed quotes after seeing your specific lot."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does it take to build a cottage in Muskoka?",
    answer: "Most custom cottages take 8-14 months from permit to move-in. Permits alone take 3-6 months depending on the township and whether you need variances. The optimal building season runs April through November. Pro tip: start in fall instead of summer—trades are more available, and winter work keeps crews busy. Just make sure the cottage is weathertight before snow flies."
  },
  {
    question: "Do you build on water-access-only properties?",
    answer: "Yes, we've completed several water-access builds. These require barge transport for all materials, which affects scheduling and costs. We coordinate with local marine services for delivery. The logistics are more complex, but the privacy and pristine locations often make it worth it. Expect to add 15-25% to your budget for water-access projects."
  },
  {
    question: "What permits do I need to build in Muskoka?",
    answer: "You'll need: 1) Building permit from your local township (Huntsville, Bracebridge, Gravenhurst, Lake of Bays, or Muskoka Lakes), 2) Shoreline development approval from the District of Muskoka for waterfront properties, 3) Septic system approval from the Health Unit, 4) Conservation authority approval if applicable. Each township has different bylaws—even the three big lakes (Muskoka, Rosseau, Joseph) have different rules. We handle all permit applications."
  },
  {
    question: "What are the shoreline setback requirements in Muskoka?",
    answer: "Setbacks typically range from 20-30 metres (66-100 feet) from the water's edge, varying by lake and township. Vegetation removal within this zone requires a Development Permit. Shoreline modification is limited to 25% of your frontage or 76 feet, whichever is less. New enclosed boathouses over water are no longer permitted in many areas—existing ones may be grandfathered. Each lake has specific rules, so verify with your township before buying."
  },
  {
    question: "Can you convert a seasonal cottage to year-round?",
    answer: "Yes, and we do it regularly. Winterizing typically involves: upgrading insulation to R-40+ (walls, attic, foundation), installing proper heating systems, upgrading electrical and plumbing for freeze protection, and sometimes foundation work. Budget $100,000-$250,000 for a full conversion. Sometimes demolishing and rebuilding makes more financial sense—we'll give you an honest assessment."
  },
  {
    question: "What's different about building in Muskoka vs the GTA?",
    answer: "Muskoka builds deal with: Canadian Shield bedrock (often requires blasting, adding $20,000-$50,000+), strict shoreline setbacks (typically 30m), well and septic instead of municipal services ($50,000-$70,000), seasonal road restrictions, and longer distances for materials. Costs run 20-40% higher than rural Ontario. Township permits can be slower. We've been handling these challenges for 9 years."
  },
  {
    question: "How much do septic and well systems cost in Muskoka?",
    answer: "Septic systems start around $25,000 for a modest 3-bedroom cottage but rise significantly for larger builds or if pump systems are required—budget $25,000-$40,000. Drilled wells typically run $25,000-$30,000. Lake water systems cost about 25% less than wells. Ensure your lot has septic approval before purchasing—some older lots can't meet current requirements."
  },
  {
    question: "Do you work with architects and designers?",
    answer: "Absolutely. Many clients come with plans from their architect, and we work with several local designers who understand Muskoka building requirements. If you don't have an architect, we can recommend people who know the unique challenges here. We're also happy to work from stock plans or help you develop a design from scratch."
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Muskoka Cottage Builder | Custom Homes Huntsville, Bracebridge, Gravenhurst" description="Custom cottage builder in Muskoka. Build costs $275-$650/sq ft. Huntsville, Bracebridge, Gravenhurst, Port Carling, Lake of Bays. 9 years experience. Free quotes.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section data-hero="dark" class="relative min-h-[70vh] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/images/projects/image00011.jpeg"
        alt="Custom cottage on Muskoka lake with waterfront view"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-black/60 via-black/50 to-black/70"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 text-center text-white pt-24">
      <p class="section-label text-white/80 mb-4">Cottage Country Experts</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-display font-medium mb-6">
        Muskoka <span class="italic">Cottage Builder</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Custom cottages and year-round homes across Huntsville, Bracebridge, Gravenhurst, Port Carling, and Lake of Bays. From $275/sq ft.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">
          <span>Start Your Muskoka Project</span>
        </a>
        <a href="tel:9057161939" class="btn-secondary border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
          Call (905) 716-1939
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Featured Snippet Target: Building in Muskoka -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">The Basics</p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
        Building a Cottage <span class="italic">in Muskoka</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="divider mb-10"></div>

      <!-- Featured Snippet Box -->
      <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-[var(--color-timber)] p-6 md:p-8 mb-10">
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] leading-relaxed">
          <strong>Building a cottage in Muskoka costs $275 to $650 per square foot</strong>, depending on quality level—20-40% higher than typical Ontario construction. The premium covers Canadian Shield bedrock (often requiring blasting), strict shoreline setbacks (typically 30 metres), well and septic systems ($50,000-$70,000), and remote material transport. Most builds take 8-14 months from permit to move-in.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-pcm text-lg">
        <p class="mb-6">
          Muskoka has been Ontario's cottage country for over a century. Three major lakes—Muskoka, Rosseau, and Joseph—plus dozens of smaller ones. Rocky shores, old-growth forests, and water clean enough to drink (though we don't recommend it).
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          Building here isn't like building in the suburbs. Bedrock sits close to the surface throughout the Canadian Shield. Shoreline regulations are strict and vary by lake. Some properties are water-access only. Winter temperatures drop below -30°C.
        </p>
        <p>
          We've been building in Muskoka for 9 years. We know which townships move quickly on permits and which ones don't. We know the reliable suppliers and the trades who show up when they say they will. We know how to build for this climate.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cost Section with Real Numbers -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Real Numbers</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          Muskoka Building <span class="italic">Costs</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">Cost Per Square Foot</h3>

          <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
            <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-2">
                <span class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">Standard Grade</span>
                <span class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-xl">$275+/sq ft</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] text-sm">Quality construction with standard finishes. Good bones, functional design.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-2">
                <span class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">Mid-Range</span>
                <span class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-xl">$410+/sq ft</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] text-sm">Upgraded finishes, custom details, quality fixtures. What most clients choose.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-2">
                <span class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">High-End Custom</span>
                <span class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-xl">$645+/sq ft</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] text-sm">Premium everything. Custom millwork, designer fixtures, architectural features.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] text-sm">
            * Architectural design adds 5-20% of project cost. Custom lighting, appliances, and landscaping are typically not included in base estimates. Budget at least 10% for landscaping.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">Additional Costs to Budget</h3>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center py-4 border-b border-[var(--color-stone)]/20">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">Septic System</span>
              <span class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">$25,000 - $40,000</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center py-4 border-b border-[var(--color-stone)]/20">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">Drilled Well</span>
              <span class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">$25,000 - $30,000</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center py-4 border-b border-[var(--color-stone)]/20">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">Lake Water System</span>
              <span class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">$18,000 - $25,000</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center py-4 border-b border-[var(--color-stone)]/20">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">Bedrock Blasting</span>
              <span class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">$20,000 - $50,000+</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center py-4 border-b border-[var(--color-stone)]/20">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">Water-Access Premium</span>
              <span class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">+15-25% of total</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center py-4 border-b border-[var(--color-stone)]/20">
              <span class="text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">Driveway Entrance Permit</span>
              <span class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">$500 - $2,000</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-8 md:p-10">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">Sample Project Budgets</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-4xl mb-2">$400K - $550K</p>
            <p class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-2">1,200 sq ft Seasonal Cottage</p>
            <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] text-sm">Standard finishes, accessible lot, 3-season use</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-4xl mb-2">$700K - $1M</p>
            <p class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-2">1,800 sq ft Year-Round</p>
            <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] text-sm">Mid-range finishes, full winterization, accessible lot</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-display text-4xl mb-2">$1.2M+</p>
            <p class="font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-2">2,500+ sq ft Custom</p>
            <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] text-sm">Premium finishes, waterfront, custom design</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Services in Muskoka -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">What We Build</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          Muskoka <span class="italic">Services</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        {services.map((service) => (
          <div class="card p-8 hover-lift group">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:bg-[var(--color-timber)] transition-colors">
              <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)] group-hover:text-white transition-colors" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d={service.icon}></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3 group-hover:text-[var(--color-timber)] transition-colors">
              {service.title}
            </h3>
            <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">
              {service.description}
            </p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a href="/services/icf-construction" class="text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium hover:underline">
          Learn more about ICF construction for Muskoka basements →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Areas We Serve -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label text-[var(--color-timber)] mb-4">Areas We Serve</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-white mb-6">
          Throughout <span class="italic">Muskoka</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
        <p class="text-white/70 max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-6">
          We build across the District of Muskoka—from the southern gateway towns to the northern reaches of Lake of Bays.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {muskokaAreas.map((area) => (
          <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 p-8 hover:border-[var(--color-timber)] transition-colors">
            <span class="text-[var(--color-timber)] text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 block">{area.highlight}</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-white mb-4">{area.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-white/60 leading-relaxed">{area.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}

        <!-- Lakes Card -->
        <div class="bg-[var(--color-timber)] p-8">
          <span class="text-white/80 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 block">Major Lakes</span>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-white mb-4">The Big Three & Beyond</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-white/90">
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-white rounded-full"></div>
              Lake Muskoka
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-white rounded-full"></div>
              Lake Rosseau
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-white rounded-full"></div>
              Lake Joseph
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-white rounded-full"></div>
              Lake of Bays
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-white rounded-full"></div>
              Skeleton Lake
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-white rounded-full"></div>
              Peninsula Lake
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Waterfront Regulations Section -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">What You Need to Know</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          Muskoka Waterfront <span class="italic">Regulations</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center mb-8"></div>
        <p class="text-xl text-[var(--color-slate)] max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Muskoka's shorelines are heavily regulated to protect water quality and natural landscapes. Here's what you need to know before buying or building.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-8">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-4">Setback Requirements</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-[var(--color-slate)]">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>Structural setbacks: 20-30 metres (66-100 feet) from water's edge, depending on lake</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>Vegetation removal within setback zone requires Development Permit</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>Shoreline modification limited to 25% of frontage or 76 feet (whichever is less)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>First 20 metres from water is critical for erosion prevention and fish habitat</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-8">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-4">Boathouse & Dock Rules</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-[var(--color-slate)]">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>New enclosed boathouses over water no longer permitted in many areas</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>Existing boathouses may be grandfathered—verify before purchasing</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>Typically need 300 feet of shoreline frontage for boathouse permit</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>May require MNRF (Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry) approval</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-8">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-4">Permits Required</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-[var(--color-slate)]">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>Building permit from local township</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>Shoreline development permit from District of Muskoka</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>Septic system approval from Health Unit</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-[var(--color-timber)] rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>Conservation authority approval (if applicable)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
